he next phase of the covid-19 vaccine rollout is expected to start in KZN on 1 May, according Premier Sihle Zikalala. The KZN Premier says he's confident the province will be able to achieve its targets. eNCA's Dasen Thathiah is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNEBURG - The next phase of the Covid-19 vaccine rollout is expected to start in KZN on 1 May, according Premier Sihle Zikalala. The KZN Premier says he is confident the province will be able to achieve its targets. Earlier Zikalala outlined the province's vaccine rollout plans. READ: KZN health workers get their jabs "With regard to the vaccination programme, the Sisonke Johnson & Johnson study, also known as 1A will resume soon and is expected to end on the 30th of April 2021," he said. "Phase 1B will commence on the 01st of May 2021 and end on the 16th of May 2021." Over 10,000 people have lost their lives to the disease in the province. The number of active cases currently stands at 4,107.